claims

Hello
My policy is W-148532 and the vehicle currently has about 133,000 Kms.  Yesterday while driving in California the check engine light came on. I didn't note any operational issues with the vehicle before or after the light came on.  Today I went to a garage here in Carlsbad, California (Carlsbad Auto Service). They read the codes indicating 3 errors, 2 related to speed sensors and 1 to thermostat.   They did not have time for further assessment and I have an appointment for Monday Dec 2nd. Please advise as to possible coverage under my warranty, is this garage acceptable to you, and any actions required on my part prior to my Monday appointment. Thank you.
Raymond Wagner


Hello 
"Raymond Wagner" <raywagner1@hotmail.com>
Have them do a complete diagnostics 
You are responsible for the diagnostics
When they have completed there diagnostics have them send a complete estimate to claims@canadageneral.ca with your policy number  in the subject line
You have coverage up to 140,000km
We will need a complete estimate before we can proceed 
If you are ok with this repair facility keep your appointment then have them contact us before they do anything 
You also have a $100.00 deductible

Kindest Regards, 

Craig Allen
